<HEADLINE>
1st LD Writethru: Tokyo stocks closed 2 pct lower
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, Sept. 11 (Xinhua)
</P>
<P>
Tokyo stocks closed nearly 2 percent lower Thursday, with the
Nikkei index hitting a six-month low.
</P>
<P>
The 225-issue Nikkei Stock Average plunged 244.13 points, or 1.
98 percent, to 12,102.50 from Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Topix index of all First Section issues on the Tokyo Stock
Exchange fell 29.66 points, or 2.49 percent, to 1,162.72.
</P>
<P>
On the First Section, declining issues outnumbered advancing
issues 1,323 to 304, with 92 others remaining unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Trading volume on the main section went down to 1,948.11 million
shares from 2,266.16 million Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The TSE's Second Section index declined 18.92 points, or 0.76
percent, to 2,470.16 on a volume of 48.02 million shares.
</P>
<P>
On the Osaka Securities Exchange, the near-term September Nikkei
225 index futures contract went down 210 points to 12,120.
</P>
